Memory - storage

Garbage collection - 

Types - 5 

Heap Memory - stores all objects and instance variables (managed by GC) : String s = new String ("Hello");


Stack Memory - stores methods calls, local variables, and references, Thread- stack, (Last In - First Out) void test(){ int x =10; y }


Method Area - class meta data, static variables,


PC Register, Native Method Stack


Why String in immutable ?

String Pool - Heap Memory


ARRAY
-----
(List of data, multiple inputs, mutable, continuous memory)

Linear Data Structure that allows to multiple values in same name 
    int x =10; int[] x = {10,11,12,13,14} //indexing starts with 0

Similar datatypes 

Fixed Length 


int[] arr; //declare 
arr = new int[5]; //allocating memory

arr[0] = 1;   //values of initialize
arr[1] = 2;
arr[2] = 3;
arr[3] = 4;
arr[4] = 5;

int arr[] = {1,2,3,4,5};   //simple

//length(); length

sum = 0

for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){
   sum = sum + arr[i]; //1+2+3
   sysout(sum);

}
    
    
String[] city = {"chennai", "Madurai", "banglore"}

city[1]; //print

